gomodel:SYNGO_5388  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4a: SynCAM 4 (CADM4) in enriched in synaptic plasma membrane biochemical fractions prepared from rat forebrain at P9 (as compared to e.g. synaptosomes), similar to SynCAM 1-3.\n\nFigure 5, 6: SynCAM 4 does not show homophilic cell adhesive interactions, unlike SynCAM 1-3, but does show heterophilic interactions with SynCAM 3, are demonstrated by cell-cell contact analysis in HEK293 cells.\n\nFigure 9: in mixed coculture assay of HEK 293 cells expressing SynCAM 1 or 2 seeded atop dissociated hippocampal cultures, SynCAM 1 and 2 recruit presynaptic marker proteins and engage each other in adhesive neuronal complexes. While this assay was not repeated for SynCAM 4 (e.g. with SynCAM 3), it is assumed that results from HEK 293 cells in Figure 6 similarly translate to cocultures.. Experimental description: most assays used brain tissue and cultures from rats:\n\"For affinity chromatography on SynCAM extracellular domains, rat forebrain homogenate was prepared in homogenization buffer\"\n\"Electrophysiological analysis was performed in primary hippocampal cultures prepared from embryonic day 18 (E18) to E19 Sprague Dawley rats.\"\n\"The indicated subcellular fractions were prepared from rat forebrain at P9.\"\n\nantibody:\n\"Antibodies against SynCAM 4 (YU591) were raised in rabbits against the peptide CGGDGHKRKEEFFI, corresponding to the C-terminal sequence of the mouse protein with an N-terminal cysteine for coupling.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5388" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

obo:UBERON_0001890  a  owl:Class .
